<p><br />
Election manifesto - list of promises by political parties to voters. Reflects the ideology + committment to voters.</p>
<h3>Benefits of Election manifesto :&nbsp;</h3>
<p><br />
1. Inform about negatives of opposition&nbsp;<br />
2. Lay out priorities in case they are voted in&nbsp;<br />
3. Educate citizens about issues like environment&nbsp;<br />
4. Highlight own achievements of the past&nbsp;</p>
<p>MCC on ELection manifesto (section 8 of MCC)<br />
1. Not repgunant to ideals of CoI&nbsp;<br />
2. DPSP allow for welfare objectives but it should compromise free and fair elections.<br />
3. financial viability must be shown</p>
<h3>New topics in manifesto&nbsp;</h3>
<p><br />
1. TN manifesto - household care, environment and farmer / fishermen rights based on protests (Unilever kodaikanal, Hydrocarbon extraction in delta reason)<br />
2. Climate disaster in poll manifesto - Day zero in chennai, Cyclones Vardah(2016) and Ockhi (2017)<br />
3. CHildren involvement in making manifesto in Assam&nbsp;</p>
<h3><br />
Conclusion&nbsp;</h3>
<p><br />
To ensure level playing field, free and fair elections, trust of voters - financial propriety is a must.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />
Political accountability = Implement poll manifesto in spirit<br />
Collective action by all political parties on problem like climate change&nbsp;</p>